reviews.text: Worst Subway that I ever visited. First it's dirty place with full of roaches at dust everywhere. Second no place to seat, or even wash your hands before to eat. Third it's hard to explain them what you want because they covered with plastic shield, looks like in jail. F....k this place don't be lazy and drive to another location.
The staff is very rude to the customers but the food is good, most of the time.

I made a order a hour ago and it said it would come in 25 to 40 minutes but I never got my order. I decided to wait a few more minutes but I still never got it. Afterwards I called and  when I asked about it they hanged up on me.

I was just in there with my husband and at first I felt bad for the guy and the girls who treated him horribly before. But my reason for this rating is due to the fact that I was in line and the guys asked me what I wanted I tries to order and he walked away and when he came back he didn't acknowledge me. Horrible customer service and he was extremely rude when my husband notified him that I was next. This is me speaking as someone who has worked in customer service for over 5 years and is currently a manager. I will never come here again.

Man I went there and asked for itailan bmt, with extra meat. Tell me why the taller hispanic woman asked me 3 times what I wanted and still got it WRONG? So I call back to have them fix there mistake, the short hispanic woman told me no you ordered spicy itailan, but she was in the back talking to the manager before he left. I told her no not what I ordered, she says drive back bring sandwich, I told her you lost your mind 7 miles back nope. Then got even more rude!  So first,  I  am not any of those customers who you can talk to crazy nor will I settle for whatever you choose to give me. Let see if corparate approves of the pictures, I took 5yrs I have order the SAME SANDWICH!!!

Fresh delicious sandwiches served by 3950, Subway Minnesota Avenue, Washington DC. Very satisfied with the food and the most friendly staffs there. Will definitely come back to try another sandwich soon.

I usually have a pleasant experience when I order drom this location. I'm an online ordering customer in order to take advantage of their deals and rewards program. I always get the veggie delight which consists of only vegetables. I always request more of certain vegetables which I typically have no issues with receiving but last night was unacceptable the way the employee, ABDUL, addressed my family as paying customers. He insulted and ridiculed us for using the online deals, deeming our order as not valued for what we were receiving, and went as far as to say "Never order from this Subway again!" And "I don't care if you make a report about me."... I was appalled and disgusted with his customer service. I've tried to reach the manager but I've been told she wasn't available. I hope they read these reviews because they are losing business at the hands of their own employees. What a disappointment!
This is the best subway. If someone interested to order party food so you can choose this subway.
The Subway 3950 is a wonderful customer service. The employees care about the customer. Their food is very fresh and delicious. They are friendly with customer. I like to eat there.

This subway is in my neighborhood. The guys that work there are awesome. You tell them what kind of sandwich you want (custom made of course) and they do exactly what you ask and an excellent job. Always friendly, polite and just fantastic. Love this place Go Visit. Minnesota Avenue NE

👎 NEVER ORDER FROM HERE! I ordered cheesy fries. The yellow stuff on my fries in the photo below was supposed to be cheese. It’s not CHEESE!  It’s some faked out shiggidy but not CHEESE. I ordered a Veggie Wrap.  The Wad of lettuce shown below is what American Best calls a wrap. It’s nothing more than a wad of lettuce in a wrap with scant sliced tomatoes. The onions and grilled mushrooms I ordered are non-existent. Take it from me, make a U turn and go to McDonald’s. You’ll at least get what you asked for from Mickey Ds.

I ordered 10 wings and fries and a cheese burger. The burger was old, the bun was soggy and burnt. The burger tasted like it was made yesterday and warmed up today. The cheese was hard. The lettuce was spoiled. You won’t have to worry about me every eating here again.  The Chicken wasn’t fresh at all. Tasted hard and over cooked like they made them yesterday or been sitting all day. Sooo GROSS!!

I use to go there all the time. The lady cashier is very nice. She gets my order right every time.  But the guy cashier is very rude, combative and racist and he acts like he doesn't like women.  I will never step my feet in there again. He told me basically he doesn't have to be professional and the is not going to do anything.

I specifically said no tomatoes on one of my wraps because I'm allergic. When I received my food at work, it had tomatoes. I called to request to pick up a new sub tomorrow since my lunch break was nearly over. The lady refused bc I couldn't bring the sandwich back today and prove it had tomatoes. Lady...you'll never get another dollar from me!

Order a 5 piece bone in with honey old bay with fries this sh. Is terrible, hard as a rock, no honey nothing. If his how they treat customers they need to close it down. I just went there for lunch on Monday and it was delicious so they need to get rid of the night cook!! I’ve learned my lesson-cook at home!!

name: Wendy's
vicinity: 4250 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text: This seems to be the only out of date Wendy’s in town, this place needs to be remodeled and up to date. The parking lot is hard to get in/out of, the parking lot holds water, it’s needs new parking spaces striping lines. I forgot to add my picture of my food, but the breakfast was hot and fresh.

The cashier had a great personality, very customer service oriented.  The manager on duty was her sister, and she engaged with customers and her Team so professionally, I'll surely be going back.  I only purchased medium french fries, and my daughter told the truth, they are absolutely freshly made and delicious!
Wonderful staff. I enjoyed talking to the staff at the register. One of the cooks gave a child two free toys I enjoy them. But the area is dark at night and sick individuals come in.
Need to do a better job at the drive through during late night hours… more night shift workers, faster pace. The lines at night are just ridiculously long for “FAST FOOD”

Only Use The Drive Through!

This place is perfectly fine if you don't go in, and don't mind longish lines in the drive thru. The food here is what you'd normally expect from Wendy's. No complaints at all with that. It's the inside that's the problem. It looks like the employees just gave up on cleaning it. Never seen such a poorly kept interior of a chain restaurant.

I love the LumberJack Slam Breakfast meal. My order was hot and tasty. Staff was friendly and helpful with Great customer service. Restaurant was clean but the parking lot parking lines needs to be repainted.

DO NOT EAT HERE!! We ordered DoorDash from here this past weekend and there were so much wrong with our order. I ordered the country fried steak that didn’t include my gravy, the eggs were watery and they didn’t put my toast in the bag. My friend got the T-bone steak (pictured) and it came RAW!!!!! The butter for his pancakes had an awful smell and his eggs were watery as well. I do not recommend eating here unless yo is joy undercooked food and missing items. Very disappointed!

Ordered the chicken fried chicken meal. The mashed potatoes were thin and liquidity and chicken was still raw in the middle. Wait staff agreed and told the manager. Manager came and disagreed but agreed to remake the chicken. By this time the rest of my food was cold then received dried overcooked chicken. Corn was good.

Horrible! I order two order of nachos, one plate had a few chips and the other one was completely soaked with oil some part rubbery and stale. This is the second time it happened to me from this location. Definitely not fresh. I spoke to the manager and all he had to say was we fry them freshly. I just threw my money in the garbage. Thanks Denny’s!

Cook at home. You can make a better Diner experience at home. The servers and cooks are awesome but the food and the atmosphere are subpar. My visits to Denny's will be very few and very far between until some real food starts being freshly prepared there and the atmosphere is a bit more upbeat and modernized.

Bland, bland, bland... cooked chicken with sauce poured on it per order? Blah, not worth the money to me! Odd ball me asked for blue cheese dipping sauce 3 separate times on my order and received none. I'm guessing it was just an odd request, right? LOL!
The chicken…hella delicious. The sides…meh not so much. The fries were mediocre at best and the Cajun rice wasn’t very Cajun. It could use some of something.

I easily ordered food from here a dozen times. The food is usually pretty good but the service can be pretty mediocre. In my most recent experience I ordered 2 catfish meals for my family. My wife noticed the catfish wasnt fully cooked. Which soured her to the idea of ordering there ever again.🤷🏿‍♂️
The fish is sooooo SMALL!! they take whole pieces of fish and cut them in HALF! you basically paying for 1 and half fish for what is supposed to be 3!!!
The one on Minnesota Avenue North East give me the wrong sandwich. I asked for chicken they give me beef. Mad as hell when I get home and call back they was closed. #263 still mad

name: Subway
vicinity: 4800 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text: This subway is great place to chilling with friends and their sandwiches are so fresh to eat . I saw so many Young person are enjoying inside of this place . Their stuff were so friendly and understanding.

It was clean and the customer service was nice. I don't usually eat subway, but the customer service was so bad and the McDonalds that I came here instead for a six inch. The sandwich was decent and I  would go back again.

New guy was wasting my time asking Double meat. I Want one layer of meat. I usually get the same thing. My son loves Black Forest Ham with lil lettuce and mayo and I get Spicy Italian or the Special of the Day. The Manager was A-Ok. He is Excellent. I use to go there often when I work 2019-2020 DC School year. The manager would fix my sandwiches perfectly. Today this new guy made me repeat my order 5 times before he got it right. Man behind me heard him.
Due to weather ( heavy snow) not crowded. We were the only 2 customers in store. Staff member was very attentive & friendly.
My sandwich was fresh and neatly made and it had just enough tuna on it without me having to ask for more. I was pleasantly surprised.

The WORST customer service I have experienced in quite sometime. A young woman walking around food with hair to her shoulders and no hair net. Two employees 1. fixing personal food at the same counter that orders are being taken & another walking around eating. Music so loud that you cannot hear.
Extremely poor environment that Govt workers patronize because of lack of choices.
Great service, atmosphere, and wonderful employees. They make you make you feel at home and show so much gratitude. If I can give them 6 Stars I would.

They are always  out of food, never properly stocked, there is hardly anything on the shelves, credit card machine is always broke and the management always makes excuses for such a poorly run business.  New management is needed!!!

This location *definitely* has a different vibe than the Bethesda location that I’m used to going to. That being said, I ordered the spring rolls and pineapple fried rice (chicken). The food was good and ready quickly. Looking forward to ordering again and trying other dishes.

If I could do 0 stars I would. I ordered Drunken noodles with beef. It was terrible… worst Thai food ever! I eat a lot of Thai food & this by far was the worst place. The presentation was great but When I took the first bite the meat had no types of flavor. Yes it had sauce on it but once you start chewing it tasted like they just put the beef in the pan to cook without seasoning it first. The sauce had a weird after taste to it too. I told my waitress I thought it was nasty & I would not like to continue eating. My friend ordered the same thing & complained as well. She took my friends plate but not mine. She had an attitude. You can clearly see she didn’t like the fact we didn’t like the food. We sat there for a few minutes wondering if she was going to take my plate too. She offered another dish but we declined. After a little I stood up went to the bar & asked to pay for the soda I drunk. She rung up the bill & added the drunken noodles I didn’t eat. I told her I ate one bite & I shouldn’t be charged for it. She yelled at me & said “everyone is eating the food! If you don’t like the food just say it”… I did tell her I didn’t like it. Hence me telling her why we weren’t going to eat our food when she took my friends plate. I eat Thai food all the time & I’ve tasted different recipes with slightly different tastes. Even with a little twist on some recipes they are great! But this place sucked man. Don’t eat here. If people say it’s good maybe they haven’t eaten authentic Thai food. Service was trash too. I walked out when the lady went to get my plate. You shouldn’t charge someone for not eating the food & start yelling at them. I said I was going to pay for the soda but she wouldn’t ring up my bill with just the soda.

Disgusting!! The red curry doesn’t even look like it has any coconut milk. For spice they used siracha in my curry. I asked for Thai chili on the side and told me twice in was in my bag when there’s wasn’t any. She put siracha in my bag instead. The pad sew shrimp had tails on it. The side of rice they give you it’s the size of your palm. Will never return and not recommended.

Ordered Tom Yum Soup Today, Feb 23rd around 12:30pm. It specifically said - NO MUSHROOMS and they added Mushrooms. When I called she said come back if you want a replacement. I said I requested for delivery for a reason, cz I cannot come there to pick it up. She said "if you don't come back with your order there is nothing I can do"
AVOID EATING HERE, ESPECIALLY IF YOU HAVE ALLERGIES.  They clearly do not care about your order specifications.
Highly disappointed  in in my lamb chops. I have ordered from this restaurant before and the meal was great. The lamb chops were very tough…not worth the $25.

I used to work around here so you know the crowd can be a lil sus throughout the day. Parking can be tight w the metro garage and street parking available. I placed an order recently for pick up and the food came out perfectly. Staff was friendly and the location was really clean. No seating inside and there is a thick fiber glass was between customers and the employees.

It’s fckin horrible I ordered a popcorn shrimp combo,ain’t received nothing I ordered but the cheesecake ain’t even get my drinks and to give me a whole box a biscuits like I’m some animal that’s very unprofessional unsavory and a rip off I paid 30$ for.biscuits mac n cheese in a size I ain’t even ordered, an honey mustard 🤦🏼‍♀️🤦🏼‍♀️🤦🏼‍♀️Someone needs to reach out and replace my food or refund me on my order
This Popeyes is very dirty we stood here for 20 mins for tenders and fries and the hygiene oh my god it’s just not it
Rude staff, rude manager, food is never up to standards! Just go a short distance down the street to the H street location. It's much better. Save your money and time and don't visit this location!

I have gotten many Uber deliveries from this location but today was the worst!  Why were my fries delivered in a bag instead of put in a fry bag and then put in the bag?  And this fish sandwich has little to no sauce on it.  In shock😔 very disappointing ‼️

I've been. Going here for jumbo cheeseburger, triple delight non spicy. I Love ❤ em Love em Love ❤ em but yesterday I ordered with my coworkers 3 wings and fried rice. The lady on phone quoted one price and quoted new price in restaurant
If was okay it took way longer than expected, but it was good the man was very polite and kind
I love Yums chicken and broccoli!!
Boost Mobile on 8th Street Northeast Washington DC is my favorite store for my phone charges screen protectors and much much more thank you boost mobile.

The food is not fresh. The lemonade ice tea taste as if it’s been sitting for days. The French fries tastes like it’s been cooked in old oil. And the cashier refused to allow refund of $4 for drinks that had only had a sip taken. She was very disrespectful. Its unbelievable how they have little to no repeat or appreciation for the community that pays their mortgages car notes and kids tuition. DO NOT BUY HERE!
McDonald's would be so much better if the staff would focus more on serving the community rather than profiling the people in the community !!
I see they got rid of all the black workers.. unless they're hidden in the back. The place was clean and the food was hot.
Food is always hot and fresh and how I ask for it! Staff works hard and respects everyone
The is hot and tasty. It's clean and sociable, I enjoy McDonald's when I need a hot tasty meal.
This is a place that I would go to for a quick cheap emergency meal. It can be dangerous most days. Food takes long dangerous people. And I know it's McDonald's but this is crazy.

Order chicken and shrimp fried rice online. They don’t have an option to add the upgrade to the fried rice online, so they will call you and the driver will bring a machine. My issue was that I asked for condiments once on my online order and then again when the guy called me to confirm my shrimp fried rice, and they didn’t give me them. I called about not receiving them and the lady on the phone goes “You don’t have hot sauce at home” RUDE. Also when they brought the card machine to my house, he gave me a receipt I went to get a pen to sign and he was gone. This receipt has a spot for a tip (which I gave online), I hope he doesn’t add anything himself.

Got chicken wings and shrimp fried rice with Gravy my chicken was old and I called the store they gonna say there chef’s said it was fresh chicken little do they know I’m calling the Better business Bureau Monday morning

Hmmmm I’m in the fence with Yum’s.  My last order wasn’t as tasty as before.  I’m not giving up on them …I want my crispy fried chicken wings back!!!!!! And the fries weren’t good so I was very disappointed.

The first time I ate here  the burger was so perfect
But this time they was in a rush to close I feel like my fires where refried because ther still and taste like cotton

I ordered  from this place Sunday.i asked  for combination lo mein and combination fried rice. The rice was so undone  it was crunchy. Literally crunchy.i asked for nothing but the beef,shrimp and chicken. I still received mushrooms and carrots.the actually lomein was dry. I paid 30 dollars.  I wish i hadn't

name: McDonald's
vicinity: 4301 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text:
How did I pay for a fish sandwich meal and two kids meal costing me over $21 and I didn’t even get my fish sandwich just my fries and drink.
And when I called the restaurant no one answers the phone.
Like seriously?
I shouldn’t have to pay for my meal and not receive it.
The person who packed my meal needs to learn to double check before giving someone their meals in the drive thu.
Oh trust and believe I will be there in the AM to speak with a manager.
Unbelievable.

NASTY MANAGER got my child’s order wrong, and insisted that he had to take the nugget happy meal he was already eating from us and put it in the trash in front of my kid before they could do give us a the right meal.   Disgusting and unprofessional location
Its was horrendous wait time. Always! Even when theres no lines. Back in the day, McDonalds mgrs always taught to pick up your feet. Now service to recv service we're on there time. Terrible
I did not get the correct change back from two different orders while ordering T the drive through window. But everything was settled after going inside and speaking to the manager.

They do not have no black people working at that establishment at all nothing but Hispanic people in a black neighborhood and I asked him why they don't have black people working there they said they are lazy and don't come to work and I was very displeased with that so I would never go back to that McDonald's ever again

OMG!! I wouldn't normally advise anyone to eat this late however, I live an unorthodox life. I work ten hour shifts, eat a light breakfast and light lunch at work; Today is my first day off and I got off of work , hangry (hungry) and tired. I normally just drink water and wake up and do breakfast but this morning, nah. I got on Uber Eats and searched for food to eat.

I've never heard of The Meltdown and ran across it on the Uber Eats app; 📣I AM NOT DISAPPOINTED!! The pictures of their cuisine, the creative/spunky names of their creations made my mouth water and my taste buds go crazy🤪 I ordered the Giddy Up Melt Combo ;  instead of fries or seasonal fruit 🍓🍑, I ordered the cucumber 🥒 salad and it was a beautiful marriage of the food and my tastebuds. I will definitely be ordering from here again! I think it's safe to say that I'm a foodie!!🤯😳

If you haven't eaten here, 📣What are you waiting for? Gone on and get your entire culinary experience with: The Meltdown. I want to personally thank all who were responsible for this delicious meal. The preparation is next level as well; Brilliant presentation and packaging.

I ordered the chicken melt meal with onion rings and beef with caramelized onion sandwich. Got home no onion rings and the sandwich wasn’t hot. Went back to get onion rings and I was given a container with 5 onion rings and sent about my business… wasted my time and gas

Cheese Steak nasty is hell.. I ask for my bread to be toast, with everything on my sandwich - tasty like mayo - only lettuce and tomatoes & Mayo - steak taste funny- $15 gone to waste. Then they don’t have no meal deals. The fries and the sandwich both was terrible. Will not go back - I will drive pass that one next time- I better not feel sick tomorrow cause the steak tasted funny af. I should have took my money to the carry-out less cheaper and way better. #MARIOS

Ledo pizza is my favorite in the city so I was so excited when I learned they were opening on East Capitol. I ordered a pizza online for dinner on the day before thanksgiving and when I arrived to pick it up, it was fresh and ready for me. At the time, it was a woman and a young man at the front but the young man was helping me. My order was ready on time so he grabbed it for me and then opened it up to show me and asked me if it looked good!! I really appreciated that level of service. The pizza was delicious per usual. I really love the square crust with the slightly sweet sauce. So damn good.

***Definitely be careful stepping down as you leave the front door though. Although there are several signs about the awkward step, you can still get got if you know what I mean.

I will definitely be ordering from this location again soon.
Omg!! The pizza is very delicious. Hot and crispy. . Chicken salad and steak and cheese soo good . The personal very friendly defendly 👍  I recommend every ones to come there 😋 👌 ☺️  😊
**UPDATE no longer a Trip hazard WHEELCHAIR AND STROLLER ACCESSIBLE ** The service was excellent and the Pizza and salad was fresh and great!!
They just open on our neighborhood and I love the pizza.

They kool people also they never follow me around the store where is this coming from
Over priced for everything bad service will follow you around in the store .If you dont trust us to shop in peace go to your live and open up a store crazy !

The chicken tasted old and dry the rice was dry and old I think the egg rolls were dry the whole meal was nasty I didn't like it wasn't like the first meal that you gave me the first meal was perfect
The food is ok service suck atmosphere the most not for me ☹

I ordered 6 general tso wings(wingettes)with rice, half steak and cheese, crab sticks and a can ginger ale (which was off brand) for $16.50. When I got my order the crab sticks were not in the bag. I called the lady said she didn't add the crab sticks to my order. I asked her to explain the charge for my order. She said they have a minimum order price of $12 and a delivery charge of $2.50. These are hidden fees unsuspecting customers like myself do not know of. Never will I order again from this place!

I wanted to give no stars but they wouldn’t let me post my comment so 1 star it is. This place is disgusting and me and my boyfriend got food poisoning and they don’t listen they just rush you and hang up they even added all this salt to my white rice and got mad because I didn’t want it I really wanna sue them don’t eat here
